          "measure": "Examining the effects of iatrogenic CI on exercise capacity",
          "description": "Each subject will undergo a full echocardiographic examination.We will assess LV systolic and diastolic function variables, mitral regurgitation, and pulmonary artery pressure.",
          "timeFrame": "24 months"
        }
      ]
    },
    "eligibilityModule": {
      "eligibilityCriteria": "Inclusion Criteria:\n\n* Able to walk on a treadmill Able to provide consent Heart failure (or not) depending upon the arm. Patients with atrial fibrillation to have had an AV node ablation (or very slow response to AF)\n\nExclusion Criteria:\n\n* Cognitive impairment, known reaction to ivabradine, musculoskeletal issues limiting walking on a treadmill.",
